  <title>Export the games</title>
  <p>
    It is possible to export and then print the games provided by the app for
    playing while not at the computer.
  </p>
  <p>
    The games will be saved in a <file>PDF</file> file in the selected folder.
  </p>
  <p>
    To export the games:
  </p>
  <steps>
    <item>
      <p>
        Choose <guiseq><gui style="menu">Game</gui><gui style="menuitem">Export Games to PDF for Off-Line Playing</gui></guiseq>.
      </p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>
        Select the type of games, the difficulty level, and how many games to export.
        When done click <gui style="button">Save</gui>.
      </p>
    </item>
  </steps>

